This script is used at the OCF to allow users to change their own ldap loginShell attribute.
For example:
sanjayk$ldapsearch -x -LLL uid=sanjayk
dn: uid=sanjayk,ou=People,dc=OCF,dc=Berkeley,dc=EDU
objectClass: top
objectClass: account
objectClass: posixAccount
objectClass: sambaSamAccount
cn: Sanjay Krishnan
uid: sanjayk
uidNumber: 18298
gidNumber: 20
homeDirectory: /home/s/sa/sanjayk
gecos: Sanjay Krishnan,The OCF,,
sambaSID: S-1-5-21-895014779-1868075160-1975190870-37596
sambaPrimaryGroupSID: S-1-5-21-895014779-1868075160-1975190870-513
sambaAcctFlags: [U          ]
sambaPwdLastSet: 1
sambaProfilePath: \\winprofiles\profiles\s\sa\%USERNAME%
loginShell: /usr/bin/tcsh
berkeleyEduCalNetUID: 646431

This database is publicly accessible, but can only be written to with an appropriate GSSAPI bind. We require that a kerberos ticket:
sanjayk$klist
Credentials cache: FILE:/tmp/krb5cc_18298
        Principal: sanjayk@OCF.BERKELEY.EDU

  Issued           Expires          Principal
Mar  9 23:34:30  Mar 10 09:34:30  krbtgt/OCF.BERKELEY.EDU@OCF.BERKELEY.EDU


Packages required:
python
python-ldap
